Hands-on packet analysis and network traffic investigation using Wireshark. This project covers protocol statistics, packet filtering, DNS analysis, conversations, endpoints, and advanced filtering techniques through practical cybersecurity lab exercises.
Wireshark Packet Operations Lab

Overview
This repository documents my hands-on learning and practical exercises focused on packet analysis using Wireshark in a controlled cybersecurity lab environment.
The objective of this project was to understand how network traffic behaves at the packet level, analyze communication flows, and use filtering techniques to investigate suspicious or relevant traffic.

