- Packet capture analysis
- Network traffic investigation
- DNS traffic inspection
- Protocol hierarchy analysis
- Endpoint identification
- Conversation tracking
- Packet filtering
- Advanced Wireshark filters
- Statistics interpretation
- Incident investigation fundamentals

Lab Tasks Completed

1. Investigating Network Traffic Captures
Loaded packet capture files (.pcapng) into Wireshark and reviewed packet-level communication.

2. Statistics Analysis
Used Wireshark Statistics tab to review:
- Capture summary
- Resolved addresses
- Protocol hierarchy
- Conversations
- Endpoints
- Packet lengths
- DNS statistics

3. Protocol Details
Inspected individual packets to understand:
- Source IP
- Destination IP
- Ports
- Protocol behavior
- Requests and responses

4. Packet Filtering Principles
Used filters to isolate relevant traffic.
Examples:
```wireshark
ip.addr == 192.168.1.1
tcp
udp
dns
http

5. Protocol Filters
Focused on specific protocols such as:
- DNS
- TCP
- UDP
- HTTP

6. Advanced Filtering
Applied advanced conditions such as:
dns.qry.name contains "google"
tcp.flags.syn == 1
ip.src == 10.0.0.5
http.request.method == "GET"

